tructors in package-private classes.\\n\\n**Examining Firestore document handling**\\n\\nI'm noticing a potential issue with the DocumentId annotation; it’s applied to the getter but not the setter, which could affect serialization. The deserialization of the DocumentId reference setter also looks fine, but I need to check if `CustomClassMapper.convertToCustomClass` accepts an immutable generic map. There could be issues with constructing Firestore classes and ensuring full access coverage. Additionally, when closing clients, I wonder if `FirestoreRpc.close` effectively shuts down channels. It seems like using a custom Firestore subclass might be worthwhile, although subclassing DocumentReference is tricky due to its constructor visibility.\\n\\n**Reviewing metadata and Java access**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I can inspect things with `javap`, but using the Gradle cache might not be necessary. It seems like we haven’t improved the metadata, which could lead to issues since dynamic reachability metadata might end up being empty, even though tests with the agent generate it. Some tasks rely on metadata files being checked, so I wonder if it’s acceptable for the metadata to be empty if the library has its own. I might need to generate and commit metadata conditionally for dynamic access in user code.\\n\\n**Considering code coverage**\\n\\nThe objective here is to focus on coverage rather than manual metadata. I’m thinking about whether to make the placeholder class public since all top-level test classes must be public, but currently, the `Google_cloud_firestoreTest` is package-private. Should we edit that? It might not really matter because we already have dedicated test files for each dynamic-access class. I wonder if removing the placeholder makes sense, especially since we aim for one-to-one mapping in our tests.\\n\\n**Addressing JUnit requirements**\\n\\nI'm considering whether JUnit requires test class methods to be public. With JUnit 5, it appears not to be a concern. However, I’m wondering if I need to compile or run tests as per the instructions. I should include that no tests ran, while also mentioning that we didn't change any untracked metadata. It's important to clarify that I didn't run the tests. There might be some hidden checkstyle rules I need to check regarding method names and class visibility.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0e16c4517a93d10c0169f77d45d178819fafe4a786c56867f1\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp931WcA6HMcZUyvsYKSyAslOkE2oo-Ok-FBoNnvYwuukqUUQvu4_IQtveIFiDs-rNudhmH17bxBDkjkJZAciHXRV2ynoWx4x_qBXq841HWahsyPodeWm_o3MVWuuA0FiZjQVXkUyBrK3gE_SN0uvYf3FAfcAYlM694HmtjSYXMPL-qM-RIDQ_Mx2A7oeduolEV7_iAZ9oNpaigCq8tW-6dnPRLTL43P68oMj-IlQ6hIlabIGhbl-bHc-mpBE1gw2l2Y7qw2Vr1NCkb4foTGQtQ8bgYHZtCxwHBGGDHIH1UxQwMR79MdWZBTboFyluh2rwm7EyVEfKP7ucnQ7zFh7STQ1_BB-xEGsOr1qT5AK6gac9Ca1KYj-KFQ6x-MLVQjNZG04HWqi8mtGyu_uXOaWgpeQ-B4kylisdz49e_avD_durXrxvIeyaqGqYgeonzmScX0XjvGm2LsvRwayZhZDbwd-N5Dg12fbHweKQBfBG9wGNYESJ-W0MFWHemdLDv6ZmwvFnkYBmTRhJ9UWeUrhxeEJOkBIBJPe8ouEtX3J8gTAxuvN_MRkMDJAVI4TRFP33AYK1Do7vLJfSNmpbzffqS7lhdtJkuwLOyKr7V22tAMhQWM1a8oKRiZEQh6q2QCQlSqcCDzBif9hey7dSp80OJOu0YmDs58sRVKitjLF-PAzDtEWa_GBJQPbsak8EBt7BTzGm-8kh2qQpm6fNs9RVW253PfYTWx0f2jgmdb6uP-26LVe2-qGXnDTNfIlBSpZ1-uZz_-Uhdwm_glqzilXlIdtm3cqADwe7LthEDgHEiGKk-qKY1932v3d2j8-42llZ5O_7fY-0VagTLLeiK4DgOIkiq5B3CbAHHjqFelvpHK8zwcfga2E4Yviyt9FbZODG-czY_Cow5QyoQIb3zCdo0cPv6fQYQuaPGisqNWq2GH-H7Ac84XWKuGwmn_42XrwnumqPeYydXG6CjHWmcdY8jLA5SOsMeZemF1M2IcC0KIOYEDCV3TxmBPfx8QiBeU_yx0nmbitbA3MbRDECQPpKJmls5ahlnsJd24T9VgEAegCcEUMAbKPFlFDONgs_Lsjw6-TqNgN18vHDgbo_pphFwzE2YHEZMlB8dgPux4WppQlN7g6hpPziUiwWJaqXXw_fCALjXXzQRvjKURYJyM5lkZNeVRzc6gk6sHH3EfA137H71BOImheWO-cxsUFzSwu8NfX8IhwdN8piuPdTG5IJC-StICmoJqHlzh_b9yaj8ziQiqi_GpbKCrbihlyV4MBvjLKl6RmVmx-uN8ZJuE-f4nnPb5u0RxC56ZMNkWmAB2Blu-BLm48QcGfd4nSVXy8HgwdNT0lU7VvqGKhj_-1dBr4Kba_OzQuhimKlXLHcFBB5hoIKprTS2-RyIhe_mxnJMgPUi44WoFvol0ijBmWICw6wN6rsIO6Imw3DP7U3lJittwhCBSm6UuXLhMc01_p